<TEXT>
Peruvian President, Alberto Fujimori has issued an order confining
all military and police to their barracks. The President is locked
in a power struggle with <TIMEX2 val="PAST_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="2000-10-25T21:33:57.97" anchor_dir="BEFORE" comment="">former</TIMEX2> intelligence service chief,
Vladimiro Monticenos. Mr. Fujimori told reporters <TIMEX2 val="2000-10-25" mod="END" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">late Wednesday</TIMEX2>, he
ordered a complete freeze on movements by the armed forces.
President Fujimori has been leading a purge of the military of those
loyal to Mr. Monticenos, the <TIMEX2 val="PAST_REF" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="2000-10-25T21:33:57.97" anchor_dir="BEFORE" comment="">former</TIMEX2> spy master, whose surprise
return to Peru on <TIMEX2 val="2000-10-23" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">Monday</TIMEX2> triggered speculation of a possible coup. 
</TEXT>
